{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"I’m a brewer’sTin’kov’s bank client a long time ago. But nuance is there. I’m using debit card\nonly. And ’cause of that I have almost…","fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"March 12, 2016","title":"Tinkoff"},"html":"<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a5563/tinkoff.avif 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/8d91f/tinkoff.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/93e07/tinkoff.webp 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/39c10/tinkoff.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/e6b01/tinkoff.jpg 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Tinkoff Black\"\n            title=\"Tinkoff Black\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Tinkoff Black</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>I’m a <del>brewer’s</del>Tin’kov’s bank client a long time ago. But nuance is there. I’m using debit card\nonly. And ’cause of that I have almost positive UX.</p>\n<p>From the latest. I’ve blocked my card 'cause of <del>stupidity</del>carelessness. After blocking the\ncard you can reissue it only but as the contract says reissue via user initiative costs 290₽. But\nfor me it was free. That is the service. In Russia. Other pros knew.</p>\n<p>Cons. Some time ago support specialist said that I shouldn’t use rough words. WTF? Tin’kov swears.\nWhere is the service? I think that a business should interact with the client in its own language.\nTinkoff says that its app is the best. But that’s not true. Sberbank caught up with it. I repeat.\nSberbank. The Russian post in the bank’s world. Synonym of fucking olds, queues, and idiotic rules,\netc. And Tinkoff can’t solve all problems via the internet. In some cases, you must send documents\nthrough regular post. I don’t know who is dumb here: law or bank. But that’s not good.</p>\n<p>I was irritated ’cause of the “PLATINUM” inscription on my debit. WTF? This is a regular MasterCard\nWorld card. I feel like a rapper with chicks, bucks, etc.</p>","id":"862d3849-9ba4-57a8-ab4e-cef33889c0aa"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"ITFarrier"}}},"pageContext":{"langKey":"en","language":"en","next":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-16-wileyfox-swift/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"Wileyfox Swift","type":null}},"previous":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-08-rieklama-v-intiernietie/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"Internet advertising","type":null}},"slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2448238595","3823719399"]}